PRIVACY POLICY
PERSONAL AND OTHER INFORMATION GAME PUBLISHER COLLECT
Personal information is information that let us know who you are and may be used to contact you online or offline, which Game Publisher will collect and acquire them with the following methods:
Information provided by you when registering for our Services, websites, jobs, products, contests, and special events; posting in or commenting on our message boards, forums, news blogs, chat rooms, or private messages; purchasing a product or services through our online stores; contacting our Customer Service directly from ticketing and e-mail.
During your visit on Game Publisher Sites or applications, we may automatically record your operating system, Internet Protocol (IP) address, access times, browser type and language and referring Web site addresses. We may use this information to monitor, develop and analyze your use of the Services.
Game Publisher can change some or all of the content / content of the service or the official website to improve the quality of the service with or without notice.
We may use this information to create a user profile and provide you with our Services. Your e-mail address may be used to contact you about your experience with Game Publisher Sites and notify you about company news and promotions. Your address may be used if we have merchandise or other physical promotional materials that we want to send to you.
In addition, your name, address, profile photo, gender, age or birthday, links to your profiles on social networking websites and other third party sites, usernames and e-mail addresses will be used by us for more personalized services, analyze user trends, and target certain promotions for you, including how we serve you based on statistic data of user characteristics. From there we will know your participation on our events and promotion, those opportunities will be used on our statistic to identifying participation frequency of our Services.
Your username will stay confidential from other users including your personal information, including any profile pictures you provided during registration, this also applies during communication process with other users.
You have the right to decline or refuse our personal information collecting methods, purpose of use, disclosure, and retention mentioned in our Policy. While you are playing Game Publisher games or applications on mobile platform, we may collect and record your device information such as the device (model or type, UDID or IMEI), MAC Address, operating system, device name, IP Address, time of access, location, phone number, and other records when using our Services.
You may choose to voluntarily provide us with various personal information and non-personal information through your use of our Services. We also may use “cookies” and other passive technologies including clear gifs to collect certain non-personal information from you in connection with your use of our Services, such as the pages you visit and the features you use. Our cookies are linked to personal information. A “cookie” is a small piece of data sent from a website and stored in a user’s web browser while the user is browsing that website. Our cookies do not include users¡¯ names, e-mail addresses, or other personal information; they are typically used to quickly identify a user’s browser, or device and to “remember” things about prior visits (such as the user’s use of various features on the service). You can disable cookies or set your browser to alert you when cookies are being sent to your computer; however, disabling cookies may affect your ability to use certain Services. A ¡°web beacon¡± is an object embedded in a web page or e-mail, which unobtrusively (usually invisibly) allows checking that a user has accessed the content.
We may occasionally send you push notifications through our mobile applications to send you game updates, high scores and other Service related notifications that may be of importance to you. You may at any time opt-out from receiving these types of communications by turning them off at the device level through your settings.
GAME PUBLISHER PURPOSES OF COLLECTING PERSONAL INFORMATION
For game account creation and access to play our games.
For protecting username and personal identification to prevent any unauthorized use of complaint or notice or reports.
For connection identification, suggestion, and communication with other Game Publisher users.
Personal information will be used in our Services operation and development which provided constantly to deliver our Services as you requested.
Comments and questions will be handled based on your information by our Customer Service.
Information provided by you will also be used on process solving any dispute, and payment refund approved or guaranteed by our Customer Service.
For better understanding of you and your preferences to improve your gaming experience and enjoyment using our Services, including other information we combined from third parties.
For delivering related information, such as confirmations, invoices, technical notices, updates, security alerts, support and administrative messages.
For promotional information including rewards, upcoming events, and other news about products and services offered by Game Publisher and our selected partners.
PERSONAL INFORMATION DISCLOSURE
Personal information collected in our Services will be used based on our Policy and the collecting process will not be done without your prior notice within our legitimate range of this Policy.
You must never share or publicly give your personal information to other users to prevent any harm or exploitation while using our Services. We will not be held responsible if anything ever happens to your personal information when you choose to share it and violating our Policy.
The Company may share your personal information with third parties as described in this Policy. The Company may share your personal information to fulfill a request you have made, such as signing up for an e-mail list or requesting customer support. In the event we offer services or promotions where your personal information is separately collected and used according to the Policy of a third party, we will inform you of that at the time of collection and you may elect not to participate in the service or promotion. In addition, we may share aggregate information (not personal information) regarding our Services usage statistics and user demographics with third parties, but this information will not include personal information.
We may share your personal information with third parties in connection with an investigation of fraud, intellectual property infringements, or other activity that is illegal or may expose you or us to legal liability, including as required by law enforcement or other government officials. We also may share your personal information with third parties when we have reasons to believe that a disclosure is necessary to address potential or actual injury or interference with our rights, property, operations, users, or others who may be harmed or may suffer loss or damage, or when we believe that disclosure is necessary to protect our rights, investigate, or enforce our terms and conditions, combat fraud and/or comply with a judicial proceeding, court order, or legal process served on the Company. In addition, your personal information may be disclosed to a potential or actual successor or assign in connection with a proposed or consummated merger, acquisition, reorganization, bankruptcy, or other similar event involving all or a portion of the Company.
PERSONAL INFORMATION RETENTION
We will retain your personal information in our Services after registration until you choose to leave our Services.
When you violate this Policy, we will give time limitation on retaining your personal information based on our internal policy.
Your personal information will be kept based on our retaining time period policy.
When you register and use our Services, we create unique profile for you into our database according to our internal policy and any law followed by us. Your personal information that will be removed including personal information, personal identification related with Services records, connection log, payment records.
Your information will no longer be available to use for any purpose when the time of removal has been set and executed.
Service log of your account will be retained based on our internal policy related with database.
PRIVACY SECURITY AND PROTECTION
We have security measurements for keeping your personal information and other users safe in our database from lost, stolen, leaked, altered or damaged. Our technical or admin department is committed to provide protection and security for your personal information.
Your personal information will be encrypted, including your user ID and password then stored and managed without the possibility to change or alter your personal identification on our Services.
Security measurements such as firewall are made to prevent any personal information damage or leakage or corruption from hacking or computer viruses, etc.
Our security measurements are supported by always maintaining best technologies available and applied them to our systems.
For more approach on our technical or admin department, this Policy is a part of personnel training to provide them with knowledge and how we are determined on giving secure system for you
